node.text:
So many little girls are taught to marry a rich man, I was taught if I became educated and worked hard- I could BE a successful woman. Whatever you tell your children, they’ll believe, whatever you tell yourself, you’ll become ✨ Inspire your kids to be great, they deserve that from you. Thank you to my parents for reminding me every single day of how capable I am, and how great I will be. I am me because of you. 
❤️ Pajamas by @nadinemerabi - Photos by @irmalomidze

node.text:
I never understand when people tell me “I always defend you!” Why exactly do you have to defend me to strangers? Is someone I don’t know actually mad at me for being an educated, young woman with multiple successful businesses that simply shares her quirky style and love for glam on social media?
🌟One day I hope people can learn the secret to life, the more negative, jealous and sh*t you talk about others the lower you’ll be in life, the more selfless kindness, happiness, and positivity towards others you spread, the universe WILL reward you.

node.text:
I really haven’t been active socially the past 3+ years, not the way I used to be anyway. I guess a part of me started to feel like it was wrong or embarrassing. My work life in general with social media has been stagnant compared to how ambitious I once was, it makes me a little disappointed in myself to let something go that deep down I not only enjoy and am good at, but I’m proud of. 
🌟 Don’t be mad at yourself for the past, you can’t change it. Focus your time on the present and the future you can change.
